snippet.title: The Diverse Mentality Podcast #96 - RIP Virgil Abloh
snippet.description:
Quake and Veto send their condolences to Virgil Abloh passing away at 41 due to cancer, Young Dolph gets buried in Memphis, victims rejecting Travis Scott's funeral payments, Trey Songz facing sexual assault charges in Las Vegas, YNW Melly's murder case trial moved up, NBA YoungBoy says he's gong to retire from music and would work with 6IX9INE, 2 Pac's hard drive is up for auction, Bobby Shmurda complains about not being in control of his music, Billboard Hot 100 update, Album sales and much more.

00:00 - Intro
00:35 - New Schedule
01:40 - RIP Virgil Abloh, Dead At 41
10:05 - Young Dolph Is Buried In Memphis.. Comedian Gets Killed For Joking About Dolph’s Death
15:32 - Family Of 9 Year Old Astroworld Festival Victim Reject Travis Scott’s Funeral Offer
25:21 - Trey Songz Investigated For Las Vegas Sexual Assault
28:11 - Fetty Wap’s Federal Drug Case Delayed Amid Plea Negotiations 
31:09 - YNW Melly’s Double Murder Trail Date Moved Up
34:17 - Quality Control Raised $100k For Atlanta Families With Food Waste Management Company
39:10 - NBA YoungBoy Has No Issues Working With 6IX9INE, Says He Wants To Retire
47:18 - 2 Pac Hard Drive Up For Auction For $1 Million Dollars
50:39 - Bobby Shmurda Says He Doesn’t Have Control Of His Music
52:27 - Album Sales
55:17 - Billboard Hot 100
58:31 - Outro
